    <h4>
        I See</h4>
    <p>
        &hellip;a timely resource to help us find life in Christ and bring life to others</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;space to allow us to expand ministry as the Lord blesses in the years ahead</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;adults, youth and children scattering on Sunday morning to their classes
        in bright, warm, inviting rooms</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;classrooms of 2 and 3 year olds, 4 and 5 year olds, 1st through 3rd grade,
        4th and 5th grade, each classroom with a sign by the door identifying the room and
        giving the teacher&rsquo;s name
    </p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a 6th to 8th grade youth group meeting in ground level</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a 9th to 12th grade youth group meeting on the 3rd floor</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;college students gathering on the first floor on a Wednesday evening to
        discuss how to stand for Christ against the rising anti-Christian sentiment on the
        WCU campus</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;cooperative ministry with Faith Church (PCA) for a Friday night youth group</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a room being used during the week by a counselor from CCEF meeting with
        a couple whose marriage is collapsing.&nbsp; His next appointment is with a young
        man from West Chester trapped in pornography.&nbsp; Next week he&rsquo;s scheduled
        to lead a group dealing with anger.</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a room being used on a weekday evening for a group of leaders from various
        churches being trained in principles of peacemaking to take back to their churches</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a group of men gathered around the conference table, coffee in hand, discussing
        how to help churches in the Presbytery in revitalization</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;people in the neighborhood drawn to the new, attractive facility of the
        church on the corner and to the hustle and bustle of activity going on there</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;the church secretary spread out in her work area, in the final stages of
        her ten hours of pulling together the bulletin and prayer lists</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a CHOP group gathered to pray for those in their life spheres and those
        in the neighborhood around the church building</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;visitors coming and staying, some curious, many convinced God is doing something
        special
    </p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a pastor deep in study in the privacy of his office, uninterrupted by people
        just passing through</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a room with heads bent in prayer, a group that gathers 6 a.m. every Tuesday
        morning to intercede for the needs of the local and broader church and for revival
        in our land</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a receptionist on site every weekday morning to answer phones, greet people,
        serving as a clearing house for urgent prayer requests and news to go out over the
        prayer net, working on special projects like making and maintaining a pictorial
        church directory, working on daily update to a dynamic RPC website</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a place where another pastoral staff person or an intern can set up shop,
        giving thought to how to minister to the youth the Lord has been bringing in</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a room with CE supplies, books, articles, outreach materials, RPC visitor
        packets, resources&mdash;all organized, retrievable, accessible</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a parlor with women of the church, drinking tea and discussing how to involve
        women more in the Word and encourage one another in their roles</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a pantry stocked with food supplies maintained by the deacons for mercy
        ministry</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;being able to say yes to the single parents&rsquo; group wanting to meet
        at RPC as part of their bi-weekly meeting rotation</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;mothers dropping their children off at a bright, clean, warm room as part
        of the Tuesday/Thursday Mothers Morning Out ministry, while they use the time to
        run errands or just get a break.&nbsp; Relationships built.&nbsp; The aroma of life
        wafts throughout.</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a volunteer putting the finishing touches on <em>The Grapevine</em>, the
        monthly RPC newsletter produced to edify and inform</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;an evangelistic Bible study meeting on Sunday evening where interested folk
        gather to discuss the gospel of Mark and be introduced to Jesus Christ</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;a Cluster group not able to meet in a home that week, gathered in February
        in warmth, discussing what Peter meant by a &lsquo;living hope&rsquo;</p>
    <p>
        &hellip;an attractive facility that shouts life by its cleanliness, brightness,
        design, and activity&mdash;an incubator for life in providing a place for teaching,
        prayer, planning, discussion, fellowship, a cultivator of life in reaching out through
        prayer, mercy ministry, study and evangelism</p>
</asp:Content>
